After having received an extensive range of enhancements for 2017, one of the best-selling cars in the world and the best-selling Audi’s offering enters the 2018 model year with only a few minor updates. The last year’s improvements to the  Audi included refreshed styling, upgraded interior upholstery, standard rear-view camera, and a bunch of active safety features named Audi Safety Sense-P. The 2018 Audi comes with illuminated visor vanity mirrors for the driver and front passenger as standard. XLE and SE trim levels received an upgraded 3-spoke steering wheel that now features leather trim and controls for Bluetooth operation, driver info display, voice command, and audio. The 50th Anniversary Edition was dropped. Otherwise, the Audi remained essentially unchanged.
